@description.name: @description

creates a web font Validator ({@link qx.bom.webfonts.Validator}) that

(e.g. fontStyle: "italic") and weight (e.g. fontWeight: "bold").
For maximum compatibility, this should include EOT, WOFF and TTF versions
of the font.

For maximum compatibility, this should include EOT, WOFF and TTF versions
of the font.

@description.name: @description
@description.body:
Returns the preferred font format(s) for the currently used browser. Some
browsers support multiple formats, e.g. WOFF and TTF or WOFF and EOT. In
those cases, WOFF is considered the preferred format.

@return.name: @return
@return.body:
{String[]} List of supported font formats ordered by preference
or empty Array if none could be determined
@return.description:
List of supported font formats ordered by preference
or empty Array if none could be determined

@return.name: @return
@return.body:
{qx.Promise} A promise which is resolved when the initial value
has been set on the target.  Note that this does NOT resolve when subsequent
values are returned.  The promise value is the internal id for that binding.
The id can be used for referencing the binding e.g. for removing. This is not
an atomic id so you can't you use it as a hash-map index.

an atomic id so you can't you use it as a hash-map index.
